{{ja-kanjitab|くるま|yomi=k}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=くるま|-}}.  Appears in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'' completed some time after 759 CE, with the ideographic spelling {{lang|ja|車}}.<ref>{{RQ:Manyoshu|4|694}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man4Yos.html#694 here]</ref>

Assuming an initial meaning of {{m|en|wheel}}, may be a compound of {{compound|ja|sort=くるま|くる|tr1=kuru|pos1=related to spinning or rotating, as in {{m|ja|繰る|tr=kuru||to spin (as in thread)}}, {{m|ja|枢|tr=kuru||hinge}}, {{m|ja|くるくる|tr=kurukuru||spinningly, round and round}}, {{m|ja|転めく|tr=kurumeku||to spin round and round, to rotate; to be dizzy}}|ま|tr2=ma|pos2=a suffix added to various parts of speech to form an indeclinable word indicating state}}.
